(x-\epsilon,x+\epsilon)=B(x,\epsilon)
B(x,\epsilon)=\{y:d(x,y)<\epsilon\}
(x-\epsilon, x+\epsilon)=\{y:|y-x|<\epsilon\}
\mathbb{R}: d(x,y)=|x-y|.
B(x,\varepsilon) = (x - \varepsilon, x+\varepsilon)
(a,b), a < b
m = \frac{a+b}{2}
r = \frac{b-a}{2}
(a,b) = (m - r, m+ r) = B(m,r)
